{"title_page": "Resting bitch face", "text_new": "{{for|the Boy George and Culture Club song|Life (Boy George and Culture Club album)}}\n'''Resting bitch face''', also known as '''RBF''', or '''bitchy resting face''' ('''BRF'''), or evening simply as JJ Glover, is a [[facial expression]] that unintentionally appears as if a person is angry, annoyed, irritated, or contemptuous, particularly when the individual is relaxed, resting or not expressing any particular emotion.<ref name=Nytimes2015-08-01>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/fashion/im-not-mad-thats-just-my-resting-b-face.html|title=I'm Not Mad. That's Just My RBF.|work=[[The New York Times]]|author=Jessica Bennett|date=August 1, 2015|page=ST9|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905131731/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/fashion/im-not-mad-thats-just-my-resting-b-face.html|archive-date=September 5, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live|quote=In that moment, I joined the ranks of a tribe of women who suffer from the scourge known as \u201cresting bitch face\u201d or, increasingly, just RBF.|author-link=Jessica Bennett (journalist)}}</ref><ref name=Washingtonpost2016-02-02>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2016/02/02/scientists-have-discovered-the-source-of-your-resting-bitch-face/|title=Scientists have discovered what causes Resting Bitch Face|work=[[The Washington Post]]|last1=Gibson|first1=Caitlin|date=February 2, 2016|access-date=February 10, 2016|url-status=live|quote=\u201cSomething in the neutral expression of the face is relaying contempt, both to the software and to us.\u201d}}</ref>[[File:Hyacinthe Rigaud- Louis XIV; Roi de France.jpg|thumb|Louis XIV, depicted by [[Hyacinthe Rigaud]] with his face resting]]The concept has been studied by psychologists and may have psychological implications related to facial [[Bias|biases]], [[gender stereotypes]], [[human judgement]], and [[decision-making]].<ref name=Psychtoday2015-08>{{cite journal|url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/intl/blog/millennial-media/201508/do-you-suffer-bitchy-resting-face|title=Do You Suffer From 'Bitchy Resting Face'?|journal=[[Psychology Today]]|first=Goal Auzeen|last=Saedi|date=August 8, 2015|access-date=December 8, 2015|url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=Arp2015>{{cite journal|url=https://50b6a48b-a-62cb3a1a-s-sites.googlegroups.com/site/chrisolivola/home/publications/Todorov%2C%20Olivola%2C%20Dotsch%2C%20%26%20Mende-Siedlecki%20%282015%29.pdf?attachauth=ANoY7cq_u_8B176APq6v8D7bhKmr5QVSemicNu7svv-9w_1WkxIs6YBFFqhwTFlFlt-jtz_urX1vMxytKovMustO-IHjlCzEJu0bGtFhIE0JeSE4GKM6ne4jMbcFmlXlAJm-COsg2FKYRzEE2SUkgfh6wV4YNL3fTNKTO5TswKi4Q2IQnYwrFs6a8_jZMNwQP_iADKC2zWGYup9vOQN8o5Zxh7xgvOPoSnFBRe7Gg4WATGvcmfhSn90Hl43lWmZPyEPCzafWv3mwn18YK-unuM23c3TzQb1qV0EeMhdv0ktr_G_c0gZcMRZnn2R8GDgDwXSVUjDNOeyI&attredirects=0|title=Social Attributions from Faces: Determinants, Consequences, Accuracy, and Functional Significance|journal=Annual Review of Psychology|last1=Todorov|first1=Alexander|last2=Olivola|first2=Christopher Y.|last3=Dotsch|first3=Ron|last4=Mende-Siedlecki|first4=Peter|year=2015|pages=519\u201345|access-date=December 8, 2015|url-status=live|volume=66|doi=10.1146/annurev-psych-113011-143831|pmid=25196277}}</ref><ref name=ScienceMic2016-02-03>{{cite news|url=http://mic.com/articles/134210/science-says-resting-bitch-face-is-real-and-you-re-probably-judging-people-for-it#.95lEIh3h9|title=Science Says Resting Bitch Face Is Real \u2014 And You're Probably Judging People for It|publisher=[[Mic (media company)|Mic]]|author=Natasha Noman|date=February 3, 2016|access-date=May 9, 2016|url-status=live|quote=In short, RBF is when a person's expression unintentionally implies they are \"simultaneously bored, mad and skeptical,\" Jessica Bennett wrote of her own face in a New York Times op-ed on the subject.}}</ref> The concept has also been studied by scientists with information technology. Utilizing a type of [[facial recognition system]], they found that the phenomenon is real and the condition is as common in males as in females, despite the gendered word ''[[bitch (insult)|bitch]]'' that is used to name the concept.<ref>Mazza, Ed. \"[http://m.huffpost.com/us/entry/us_56b2d1e0e4b04f9b57d87c44 Science Finds Resting Bitch Face Is Real -- And Men Can Have It, Too]\", [[Huffington Post]] (February 4, 2016): \"While there has been a certain amount of sexism surrounding resting bitch face -- even the name itself is laced with it -- the computer detected RBF as frequently in men as it did in women.\"</ref>\n\n==Origin==\nIn a 2013 year-end round-up of newly popular words and phrases, ''[[New York Times|The New York Times]]'' writer [[Grant Barrett]] asserted that the phrase dates back \"at least ten years\".<ref name=Nytimes2013-12-22>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/22/opinion/sunday/a-wordnado-of-words-in-2013.html|title=A Wordnado of Words in 2013|work=[[The New York Times]]|author=Grant Barrett|date=December 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418092139/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/22/opinion/sunday/a-wordnado-of-words-in-2013.html|archive-date=April 18, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Dating back at least 10 years as a described concept but popularized in 2013 by a video made by the group Broken People.}}</ref> \n\nOn May 22, 2013, the comedy group Broken People uploaded a parody [[public service announcement]] video titled \"Bitchy Resting Face\" (BRF) on the [[Funny or Die]] website in which male and female \"sufferers\" of an annoyed-looking [[blank expression]] ask for understanding from non-sufferers.<ref name=YouTubeBitchyRestingFaceVideo>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3v98CPXNiSk|title=Bitchy resting face|publisher=Broken People|date=May 22, 2013|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> It has since gone on to become a popular [[Internet meme]], and to become more commonly known as Resting Bitch Face (RBF).<ref name=\"Nytimes2015-08-01\"/>\n\n==Spread in wider culture==\nThe term has become widely referred to in the media. It has made its way into lifestyle and fashion magazines for women such as [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|''Cosmopolitan'']] and [[Elle (magazine)|''Elle'']], and been mentioned in published literature, both fiction and non-fiction.<ref name=Cosmopolitan2015-06-04>{{cite news|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/lifestyle/news/a41460/struggles-women-with-resting-bitch-face-understand/|title=13 Struggles Only Women With Resting Bitch Face Understand|work=[[Cosmopolitan magazine]]|author=Stephanie Shi|date=June 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930054623/http://www.cosmopolitan.com/lifestyle/news/a41460/struggles-women-with-resting-bitch-face-understand/|archive-date=September 30, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Elle2014-02-05>{{cite news|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/news/a15323/resting-bitch-face-syndrome|title=I won't apologize for my 'bitchy resting face'|work=[[Elle magazine]]|author=Kristina Rodulfo|date=February 5, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201210429/http://www.elle.com/culture/news/a15323/resting-bitch-face-syndrome|archive-date=February 1, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Blindsided>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0vnFBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA15|title=Blindsided|publisher=Butterfly Publishing|first=Holly|last=Mortimer|year=2015|page=15|location=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|url-status=live|quote=|isbn=9781508448983}}</ref><ref name=Chictionary>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=iCTnBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT22&dq=resting+bitch+face#v=onepage&q=resting%20bitch%20face&f=false|title=Chic-tionary: The Little Book of Fashion Faux-cabulary|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing|first=Stephanie|last=Simons|location=New York|year=2014|section=2|url-status=live|isbn=9781629145464}}</ref><ref name=EOnline2015-08-04>{{cite news|url=http://ca.eonline.com/news/682992/kristen-stewart-responds-to-accusations-that-she-suffers-from-resting-bitch-face-i-actually-smile-a-lot|title=Kristen Stewart Responds to Accusations That She Suffers From Resting Bitch Face: \"I Actually Smile a Lot!\"|publisher=[[E! Online]]|author=Zach Johnson|date=August 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151111180056/http://www.eonline.com/news/682992/kristen-stewart-responds-to-accusations-that-she-suffers-from-resting-bitch-face-i-actually-smile-a-lot|archive-date=November 11, 2015|access-date=August 6, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Kristen Stewart may not have a permanent grin on her face, \u00e0 la Tom Cruise on a worldwide promo tour, but the actress doesn't suffer from resting bitch face, either. In fact, Stewart is tired of people assuming she's always unhappy. \"The whole smiling thing is weird because I actually smile a lot,\" the actress admitted. \"I literally want to be like, 'Dude, you would think I was cool if you got to know me.'\"}}</ref> \n\n[[Hadley Freeman]] wrote that since it appeared in the Broken People video, it had enjoyed a stratospheric rise, and pointed out that the male equivalent term Resting Asshole Face (RAF) highlighted in this video had not received the same degree of comment.<ref name=Guardian2013-07-23>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/jul/23/bitchy-resting-face-aimed-women|title=Bitchy resting face: must it be taken so seriously?|first=Hadley|last=Freeman|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=July 23, 2013|url-status=live }}</ref> Texas Women's University academic Rene Paulson stated that those with resting bitch face have a stronger sense of self-awareness and a better ability to communicate,<ref name=Marieclare2015-09-09>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.marieclaire.com/beauty/news/a15807/resting-bitch-face-good-for-you-study/|title=Resting Bitch Face Actually Makes You Better, Says Science|journal=[[Marie Claire]]|first=Lauren|last=Valenti|date=September 9, 2015|url-status=live }}</ref> whilst [[New York University]] psychologist Jonathan Freeman carried out a study showing that slightly angry facial expressions make other people think you are untrustworthy.<ref name=Quartz2015-09-06>{{cite news|url=http://qz.com/495771/women-with-resting-bitch-face-are-actually-better-communicators/|title=Women with \"resting bitch face\" are actually better communicators|work=[[Quartz (magazine)|Quartz]]|author=Rene Paulson|date=September 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907120145/http://qz.com/495771/women-with-resting-bitch-face-are-actually-better-communicators/|archive-date=September 7, 2015|access-date=November 12, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Research has shown that people rely heavily on facial expressions and body language. Psychologist Albert Mehrabian (...) conducted famous studies in the 1960s that found that interpreting someone\u2019s communication is based mostly on nonverbal cues, like facial expression, body language and tone. Women confronted by a world that automatically attaches negative attributes to their non-smiling face must quickly learn how to communicate and also hone a finely-tuned awareness of both our own emotions and the emotions of those around us.}}</ref><ref name=SageJournals2015-06-18>{{cite news|title=Static and Dynamic Facial Cues Differentially Affect the Consistency of Social Evaluations|date=June 18, 2015|doi=10.1177/0146167215591495}}</ref>\n\nChlo\u00e9 Hogg, in a 2014 article in the journal ''[[Philological Quarterly]]'', asserted that the phenomenon was not new, and offered [[Hyacinthe Rigaud]]'s portrait of [[Louis XIV of France]] depicting his \"bitchy resting face\".<ref name=PhiloQuarterly>{{cite journal|url=http://search.proquest.com/openview/1c21559c9442a1776b13020a3db72023/1?pq-origsite=gscholar|title=Subject of Passions: Charles Le Brun and the Emotions of Absolutism|journal=[[Philological Quarterly]]|author=Chlo\u00e9 Hogg|date=Winter 2014|pages=65\u201394|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fsearch.proquest.com%2Fopenview%2F1c21559c9442a1776b13020a3db72023%2F1%3Fpq-origsite%3Dgscholar&date=2015-11-11|archive-date=November 11, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Hyacinthe Rigaud's famous portrait of Louis XIV depicts the absolute monarch's absolute physiognomic control as part of the attributes of royalty-what I'm tempted to call, in contemporary emotional parlance, Louis XIV's ''\"bitchy resting face\"''.}}</ref> Levels of resting bitch face can vary greatly with different magnitudes and amounts of fierceness.\n\nIn 2015, [[CBS News]] reported that some plastic surgeons were using plastic surgery to help patients with RBF.<ref name=CbsNews2015-10-26>{{cite news|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/10/26/resting-bitch-face-cosmetic-treatment/|title=Seen At 11: A Cosmetic Cure For 'Resting Bitch Face'|publisher=[[CBS News]]|date=October 26, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151027161401/http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/10/26/resting-bitch-face-cosmetic-treatment|archive-date=October 27, 2015|access-date=November 12, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=CbsUndated1>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/13-bizarre-but-popular-plastic-surgery-procedures/3/|title=13 bizarre but popular plastic surgery procedures|publisher=[[CBS News]]|date=October 26, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511213332/http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/13-bizarre-but-popular-plastic-surgery-procedures/3/|archive-date=May 11, 2015|access-date=November 12, 2015|url-status=live|quote=According to Dr. Joseph Eviatar of Chelsea Cosmetic, more and more people are seeking medical treatment to help correct their natural resting bitch face.}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, comedian [[Andrew Doyle (comedian)|Andrew Doyle]] stated that he had cast actress Alice Marshall as his character [[Titania McGrath]], in part because she could convincingly pull off Titania's Resting Bitch Face.<ref name=Telegraph2019-07-26>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comedy/what-to-see/created-monster-woke-warrior-titania-mcgrath-now-bringing/|title=I created a monster in 'woke' warrior Titania McGrath \u2013 and now I'm bringing her to life onstage|publisher=The Telegraph|date=July 26, 2019|access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Facial feedback hypothesis]]\n* [[Social identity theory]]\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.funnyordie.com/videos/d7ab80d4a5/bitchy-resting-face \"Bitchy Resting Face\" on Funny or Die] ([[MP4]]) {{plays audio}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Facial expressions]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Boy George and Culture Club song|Life (Boy George and Culture Club album)}}\n'''Resting bitch face''', also known as '''RBF''', or '''bitchy resting face''' ('''BRF'''), is a [[facial expression]] that unintentionally appears as if a person is angry, annoyed, irritated, or contemptuous, particularly when the individual is relaxed, resting or not expressing any particular emotion.<ref name=Nytimes2015-08-01>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/fashion/im-not-mad-thats-just-my-resting-b-face.html|title=I'm Not Mad. That's Just My RBF.|work=[[The New York Times]]|author=Jessica Bennett|date=August 1, 2015|page=ST9|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905131731/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/02/fashion/im-not-mad-thats-just-my-resting-b-face.html|archive-date=September 5, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live|quote=In that moment, I joined the ranks of a tribe of women who suffer from the scourge known as \u201cresting bitch face\u201d or, increasingly, just RBF.|author-link=Jessica Bennett (journalist)}}</ref><ref name=Washingtonpost2016-02-02>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2016/02/02/scientists-have-discovered-the-source-of-your-resting-bitch-face/|title=Scientists have discovered what causes Resting Bitch Face|work=[[The Washington Post]]|last1=Gibson|first1=Caitlin|date=February 2, 2016|access-date=February 10, 2016|url-status=live|quote=\u201cSomething in the neutral expression of the face is relaying contempt, both to the software and to us.\u201d}}</ref>[[File:Hyacinthe Rigaud- Louis XIV; Roi de France.jpg|thumb|Louis XIV, depicted by [[Hyacinthe Rigaud]] with his face resting]]The concept has been studied by psychologists and may have psychological implications related to facial [[Bias|biases]], [[gender stereotypes]], [[human judgement]], and [[decision-making]].<ref name=Psychtoday2015-08>{{cite journal|url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/intl/blog/millennial-media/201508/do-you-suffer-bitchy-resting-face|title=Do You Suffer From 'Bitchy Resting Face'?|journal=[[Psychology Today]]|first=Goal Auzeen|last=Saedi|date=August 8, 2015|access-date=December 8, 2015|url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=Arp2015>{{cite journal|url=https://50b6a48b-a-62cb3a1a-s-sites.googlegroups.com/site/chrisolivola/home/publications/Todorov%2C%20Olivola%2C%20Dotsch%2C%20%26%20Mende-Siedlecki%20%282015%29.pdf?attachauth=ANoY7cq_u_8B176APq6v8D7bhKmr5QVSemicNu7svv-9w_1WkxIs6YBFFqhwTFlFlt-jtz_urX1vMxytKovMustO-IHjlCzEJu0bGtFhIE0JeSE4GKM6ne4jMbcFmlXlAJm-COsg2FKYRzEE2SUkgfh6wV4YNL3fTNKTO5TswKi4Q2IQnYwrFs6a8_jZMNwQP_iADKC2zWGYup9vOQN8o5Zxh7xgvOPoSnFBRe7Gg4WATGvcmfhSn90Hl43lWmZPyEPCzafWv3mwn18YK-unuM23c3TzQb1qV0EeMhdv0ktr_G_c0gZcMRZnn2R8GDgDwXSVUjDNOeyI&attredirects=0|title=Social Attributions from Faces: Determinants, Consequences, Accuracy, and Functional Significance|journal=Annual Review of Psychology|last1=Todorov|first1=Alexander|last2=Olivola|first2=Christopher Y.|last3=Dotsch|first3=Ron|last4=Mende-Siedlecki|first4=Peter|year=2015|pages=519\u201345|access-date=December 8, 2015|url-status=live|volume=66|doi=10.1146/annurev-psych-113011-143831|pmid=25196277}}</ref><ref name=ScienceMic2016-02-03>{{cite news|url=http://mic.com/articles/134210/science-says-resting-bitch-face-is-real-and-you-re-probably-judging-people-for-it#.95lEIh3h9|title=Science Says Resting Bitch Face Is Real \u2014 And You're Probably Judging People for It|publisher=[[Mic (media company)|Mic]]|author=Natasha Noman|date=February 3, 2016|access-date=May 9, 2016|url-status=live|quote=In short, RBF is when a person's expression unintentionally implies they are \"simultaneously bored, mad and skeptical,\" Jessica Bennett wrote of her own face in a New York Times op-ed on the subject.}}</ref> The concept has also been studied by scientists with information technology. Utilizing a type of [[facial recognition system]], they found that the phenomenon is real and the condition is as common in males as in females, despite the gendered word ''[[bitch (insult)|bitch]]'' that is used to name the concept.<ref>Mazza, Ed. \"[http://m.huffpost.com/us/entry/us_56b2d1e0e4b04f9b57d87c44 Science Finds Resting Bitch Face Is Real -- And Men Can Have It, Too]\", [[Huffington Post]] (February 4, 2016): \"While there has been a certain amount of sexism surrounding resting bitch face -- even the name itself is laced with it -- the computer detected RBF as frequently in men as it did in women.\"</ref>\n\n==Origin==\nIn a 2013 year-end round-up of newly popular words and phrases, ''[[New York Times|The New York Times]]'' writer [[Grant Barrett]] asserted that the phrase dates back \"at least ten years\".<ref name=Nytimes2013-12-22>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/22/opinion/sunday/a-wordnado-of-words-in-2013.html|title=A Wordnado of Words in 2013|work=[[The New York Times]]|author=Grant Barrett|date=December 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418092139/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/22/opinion/sunday/a-wordnado-of-words-in-2013.html|archive-date=April 18, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Dating back at least 10 years as a described concept but popularized in 2013 by a video made by the group Broken People.}}</ref> \n\nOn May 22, 2013, the comedy group Broken People uploaded a parody [[public service announcement]] video titled \"Bitchy Resting Face\" (BRF) on the [[Funny or Die]] website in which male and female \"sufferers\" of an annoyed-looking [[blank expression]] ask for understanding from non-sufferers.<ref name=YouTubeBitchyRestingFaceVideo>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3v98CPXNiSk|title=Bitchy resting face|publisher=Broken People|date=May 22, 2013|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> It has since gone on to become a popular [[Internet meme]], and to become more commonly known as Resting Bitch Face (RBF).<ref name=\"Nytimes2015-08-01\"/>\n\n==Spread in wider culture==\nThe term has become widely referred to in the media. It has made its way into lifestyle and fashion magazines for women such as [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|''Cosmopolitan'']] and [[Elle (magazine)|''Elle'']], and been mentioned in published literature, both fiction and non-fiction.<ref name=Cosmopolitan2015-06-04>{{cite news|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/lifestyle/news/a41460/struggles-women-with-resting-bitch-face-understand/|title=13 Struggles Only Women With Resting Bitch Face Understand|work=[[Cosmopolitan magazine]]|author=Stephanie Shi|date=June 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930054623/http://www.cosmopolitan.com/lifestyle/news/a41460/struggles-women-with-resting-bitch-face-understand/|archive-date=September 30, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Elle2014-02-05>{{cite news|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/news/a15323/resting-bitch-face-syndrome|title=I won't apologize for my 'bitchy resting face'|work=[[Elle magazine]]|author=Kristina Rodulfo|date=February 5, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201210429/http://www.elle.com/culture/news/a15323/resting-bitch-face-syndrome|archive-date=February 1, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Blindsided>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0vnFBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA15|title=Blindsided|publisher=Butterfly Publishing|first=Holly|last=Mortimer|year=2015|page=15|location=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|url-status=live|quote=|isbn=9781508448983}}</ref><ref name=Chictionary>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=iCTnBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT22&dq=resting+bitch+face#v=onepage&q=resting%20bitch%20face&f=false|title=Chic-tionary: The Little Book of Fashion Faux-cabulary|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing|first=Stephanie|last=Simons|location=New York|year=2014|section=2|url-status=live|isbn=9781629145464}}</ref><ref name=EOnline2015-08-04>{{cite news|url=http://ca.eonline.com/news/682992/kristen-stewart-responds-to-accusations-that-she-suffers-from-resting-bitch-face-i-actually-smile-a-lot|title=Kristen Stewart Responds to Accusations That She Suffers From Resting Bitch Face: \"I Actually Smile a Lot!\"|publisher=[[E! Online]]|author=Zach Johnson|date=August 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151111180056/http://www.eonline.com/news/682992/kristen-stewart-responds-to-accusations-that-she-suffers-from-resting-bitch-face-i-actually-smile-a-lot|archive-date=November 11, 2015|access-date=August 6, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Kristen Stewart may not have a permanent grin on her face, \u00e0 la Tom Cruise on a worldwide promo tour, but the actress doesn't suffer from resting bitch face, either. In fact, Stewart is tired of people assuming she's always unhappy. \"The whole smiling thing is weird because I actually smile a lot,\" the actress admitted. \"I literally want to be like, 'Dude, you would think I was cool if you got to know me.'\"}}</ref> \n\n[[Hadley Freeman]] wrote that since it appeared in the Broken People video, it had enjoyed a stratospheric rise, and pointed out that the male equivalent term Resting Asshole Face (RAF) highlighted in this video had not received the same degree of comment.<ref name=Guardian2013-07-23>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/jul/23/bitchy-resting-face-aimed-women|title=Bitchy resting face: must it be taken so seriously?|first=Hadley|last=Freeman|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=July 23, 2013|url-status=live }}</ref> Texas Women's University academic Rene Paulson stated that those with resting bitch face have a stronger sense of self-awareness and a better ability to communicate,<ref name=Marieclare2015-09-09>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.marieclaire.com/beauty/news/a15807/resting-bitch-face-good-for-you-study/|title=Resting Bitch Face Actually Makes You Better, Says Science|journal=[[Marie Claire]]|first=Lauren|last=Valenti|date=September 9, 2015|url-status=live }}</ref> whilst [[New York University]] psychologist Jonathan Freeman carried out a study showing that slightly angry facial expressions make other people think you are untrustworthy.<ref name=Quartz2015-09-06>{{cite news|url=http://qz.com/495771/women-with-resting-bitch-face-are-actually-better-communicators/|title=Women with \"resting bitch face\" are actually better communicators|work=[[Quartz (magazine)|Quartz]]|author=Rene Paulson|date=September 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907120145/http://qz.com/495771/women-with-resting-bitch-face-are-actually-better-communicators/|archive-date=September 7, 2015|access-date=November 12, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Research has shown that people rely heavily on facial expressions and body language. Psychologist Albert Mehrabian (...) conducted famous studies in the 1960s that found that interpreting someone\u2019s communication is based mostly on nonverbal cues, like facial expression, body language and tone. Women confronted by a world that automatically attaches negative attributes to their non-smiling face must quickly learn how to communicate and also hone a finely-tuned awareness of both our own emotions and the emotions of those around us.}}</ref><ref name=SageJournals2015-06-18>{{cite news|title=Static and Dynamic Facial Cues Differentially Affect the Consistency of Social Evaluations|date=June 18, 2015|doi=10.1177/0146167215591495}}</ref>\n\nChlo\u00e9 Hogg, in a 2014 article in the journal ''[[Philological Quarterly]]'', asserted that the phenomenon was not new, and offered [[Hyacinthe Rigaud]]'s portrait of [[Louis XIV of France]] depicting his \"bitchy resting face\".<ref name=PhiloQuarterly>{{cite journal|url=http://search.proquest.com/openview/1c21559c9442a1776b13020a3db72023/1?pq-origsite=gscholar|title=Subject of Passions: Charles Le Brun and the Emotions of Absolutism|journal=[[Philological Quarterly]]|author=Chlo\u00e9 Hogg|date=Winter 2014|pages=65\u201394|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fsearch.proquest.com%2Fopenview%2F1c21559c9442a1776b13020a3db72023%2F1%3Fpq-origsite%3Dgscholar&date=2015-11-11|archive-date=November 11, 2015|access-date=August 2, 2015|url-status=live|quote=Hyacinthe Rigaud's famous portrait of Louis XIV depicts the absolute monarch's absolute physiognomic control as part of the attributes of royalty-what I'm tempted to call, in contemporary emotional parlance, Louis XIV's ''\"bitchy resting face\"''.}}</ref> Levels of resting bitch face can vary greatly with different magnitudes and amounts of fierceness.\n\nIn 2015, [[CBS News]] reported that some plastic surgeons were using plastic surgery to help patients with RBF.<ref name=CbsNews2015-10-26>{{cite news|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/10/26/resting-bitch-face-cosmetic-treatment/|title=Seen At 11: A Cosmetic Cure For 'Resting Bitch Face'|publisher=[[CBS News]]|date=October 26, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151027161401/http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/10/26/resting-bitch-face-cosmetic-treatment|archive-date=October 27, 2015|access-date=November 12, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=CbsUndated1>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/13-bizarre-but-popular-plastic-surgery-procedures/3/|title=13 bizarre but popular plastic surgery procedures|publisher=[[CBS News]]|date=October 26, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511213332/http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/13-bizarre-but-popular-plastic-surgery-procedures/3/|archive-date=May 11, 2015|access-date=November 12, 2015|url-status=live|quote=According to Dr. Joseph Eviatar of Chelsea Cosmetic, more and more people are seeking medical treatment to help correct their natural resting bitch face.}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, comedian [[Andrew Doyle (comedian)|Andrew Doyle]] stated that he had cast actress Alice Marshall as his character [[Titania McGrath]], in part because she could convincingly pull off Titania's Resting Bitch Face.<ref name=Telegraph2019-07-26>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comedy/what-to-see/created-monster-woke-warrior-titania-mcgrath-now-bringing/|title=I created a monster in 'woke' warrior Titania McGrath \u2013 and now I'm bringing her to life onstage|publisher=The Telegraph|date=July 26, 2019|access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Facial feedback hypothesis]]\n* [[Social identity theory]]\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.funnyordie.com/videos/d7ab80d4a5/bitchy-resting-face \"Bitchy Resting Face\" on Funny or Die] ([[MP4]]) {{plays audio}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Facial expressions]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n", "name_user": "Imissthewtcnorthtower", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resting_bitch_face"}
{"title_page": "Abba Kyari (politician)", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{For|the Nigerian Army Brigadier who served as Governor of North-Central State|Abba Kyari (military general)}}\n{{short description|Nigerian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox Officeholder\n| name                = Abba Kyari\n| image               = Abba-Kyari2.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date|1952|09|23|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Borno State|Borno]], [[Northern Region, Nigeria|Northern Region]], [[British Nigeria]]<br>(now [[Borno State]], Nigeria)\n| death_date          = {{Death date and age|2020|4|17|1952|09|23|df=y}}\n| office1             = [[Chief of Staff to the President (Nigeria)| Chief of  Staff to the President]]\n| president1          = [[Muhammadu Buhari]]\n| term_start1         = 27 August 2015\n| term_end1           = 17 April 2020\n| predecessor1        = Jones Arogbofa\n| alma_mater          = [[Nigerian Law School]]<br>[[Harvard Business School]]<br>[[International Institute for Management Development]]\n| education           = [[University of Warwick]]<br>[[University of Cambridge]]\n| awards              = [[Order of the Niger]]\n| death_place         = [[Lagos]], Nigeria\n| honorific_suffix    = [[Order of the Niger|OON]]\n| spouse              = Hajiya Kulu Kyari\n| children            = 4\n}}\n\n'''Abba Kyari''' [[Order of the Niger|OON]] (23 September 1952 \u2013 17 April 2020)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/top-news/388646-exclusive-abba-kyaris-real-date-of-birth-uncovered.html |title=EXCLUSIVE: Abba Kyari's real date of birth uncovered |work=[[Premium Times]] |last=Ogundipe |first=Samuel |date=2020-04-18 |language=en-GB |access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> was a Nigerian Politician who served as Chief of Staff to [[President of Nigeria|President]] [[Muhammadu Buhari]].<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|last1=Bakare|first1=Tonye|title=Buhari appoints Lawal as SGF, Kyari as CoS|url=http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/2015/08/flash-buhari-appoints-lawal-as-sgf/|website=Guardian Nigeria|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Family and personal life==\n\n=== Early life and education ===\nKyari was born on 23 September 1952, to a [[Kanuri people|Kanuri]] family from [[Borno State|Borno]]. He was educated in St. Paul\u2019s College in [[Wusasa]], and later considered joining the [[Nigerian Army]] following advice from [[Mamman Daura]] and [[Ibrahim Tahir]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/opinion/columnists/ibrahim-tahir-a-personal-loss-2/|title=Ibrahim Tahir: A Personal Loss|last=Kyari|first=Abba|date=23 December 2009|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 1976, he met General [[Muhammadu Buhari]] who was then [[Governor of Borno State]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/features/for-the-record/to-my-friend-mallam-abba-kyari-buhari/|title=To my friend, Mallam Abba Kyari \u2013 Buhari|last=Buhari|first=Muhammadu|date=18 April 2020|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 1980, he graduated with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[sociology]] from the [[University of Warwick]], and also received a bachelor's degree in [[law]] from the [[University of Cambridge]].<ref name=\"Exxon-Mobil2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.exxonmobil.com.ng/Nigeria-English/PA/products_downstream_directors.aspx|title=Exxon Mobil Nigeria Board of Directors|website=Exxon Mobil|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref> In 1983, he was called to the [[Nigerian Bar Association|Nigerian Bar]] after attending the [[Nigerian Law School]].<ref name=\"TDLN\">{{cite web|last1=Aboyade |first1=Funke |title=From Dublin, Law School Set of \u201983 Plans Big |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/from-dublin-law-school-set-of-8217-83-plans-big/127530 |website=This Day Live Nigeria |accessdate=29 August 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016010128/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/from-dublin-law-school-set-of-8217-83-plans-big/127530 |archivedate=16 October 2012 }}</ref> \n\nIn 1984, he obtained a [[master's degree]] in law from the University of Cambridge.<ref name=\"Exxon-Mobil\">{{cite web|title=Exxon Mobil Nigeria Board of Directors|url=http://www.exxonmobil.com.ng/Nigeria-English/PA/products_downstream_directors.aspx|website=Exxon Mobil|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref> He later attended the [[International Institute for Management Development]] in [[Lausanne]], Switzerland and participated in the Program for Management Development at the [[Harvard Business School]], in 1992 and 1994, respectively.\n\n=== Family ===\nKyari was married to the sister-in-law of [[Ibrahim Tahir]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gamji.com/haruna/haruna303.htm|title=Tahir: The Death of a Radical Conservative|last=Haruna|first=Mohammed|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and had four children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/opinion/columnists/ibrahim-tahir-a-personal-loss-2/|title=Ibrahim Tahir: A Personal Loss|last=Kyari|first=Abba|date=23 December 2009|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Health ===\nOn 24 March 2020, it was made public that Kyari tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] on 23 March, following an official trip to Germany nine days before.<ref name=coronavirus>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/383571-coronavirus-abba-kyari-reportedly-tests-positive-kingibe-others-may-be-tested.html|title=UPDATED: Coronavirus: Abba Kyari reportedly tests positive; Kingibe, others may be tested|last=Owoseye|first=Ayodamola|date=2020-03-24|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> There were reports that he had been flown out of the country for treatment<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://desertherald.com/exclusive-buharis-chief-of-staff-abba-kyari-admitted-at-londons-hospital/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Buhari\u2019s Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari Admitted at London\u2019s Hospital|last=Herald|first=Desert|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>, and [[Reuters]] later reported he had \"a history of medical complications, including [[diabetes]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nigeria-idUSKBN21B1OT|title=Top Nigerian president aide, state governor test positive for coronavirus|date=2020-03-24|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-18|language=en}}</ref> On 29 March 2020, in an official statement, Kyari annouced he was being moved from isolation in [[Abuja]] to [[Lagos]] for \"preventive treatment\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/covid-19-why-i-moved-to-lagos-after-testing-positive-abba-kyari.html|title=Covid-19: Why I moved to Lagos after testing positive - Abba Kyari|date=2020-03-29|website=Daily Trust|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Professional career ==\nKyari worked for the law firm Fani-Kayode and Sowemimo for some time after his return to Nigeria.<ref name=\"Naij-FFK\">{{cite web|last1=Bolashodun|first1=Oluwatobi|title=Fani-Kayode Reacts To Abba Kyari's Appointment|url=https://www.naij.com/532624-read-fani-kayodes-reaction-abba-kyaris-appointment-buharis-cos.html|website=Naij|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>  \n\nFrom 1988 to 1990, he was Editor with the New Africa Holdings Limited Kaduna.  \n\nIn 1990, he served as a Commissioner for Forestry and Animal Resources in [[Borno State]].  \n\nFrom 1990 to 1995, Kyari was the secretary to the board of African International Bank Limited, a subsidiary of [[Bank of Credit and Commerce International]]. \n\nKyari was an executive director in charge of management services at the [[United Bank for Africa]], and was later appointed the [[chief executive officer]]. In 2002, he was appointed a board director of [[Unilever Nigeria Plc|Unilever Nigeria]], and later served on the board of [[ExxonMobil|Exxon Mobil]] Nigeria.\n\n== Political career ==\nIn August 2015, Kyari was appointed [[Chief of Staff to the President (Nigeria)|Chief of Staff]] to [[President of Nigeria|President]] [[Muhammadu Buhari]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoguideafrica.com/2020/04/Abba-Kyari.html|title=Mallam Abba Kyari Biography, Age, Early Life, Family, Net Worth And More|last=Stanford|first=Igbo|website=Information Guide Africa|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/189095-breaking-buhari-appoints-sgf-chief-of-staff-others.html|title=Buhari appoints SGF, Chief of Staff, others - Premium Times Nigeria|date=2015-08-27|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n=== Power politics ===\nKyari was an influential figure within the Buhari administration.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punchng.com/men-of-power-nigerias-most-influential-power-brokers/|title=Men of power: Nigeria\u2019s most influential power brokers|last=Published|website=Punch Newspapers|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> During the administration's first term, he worked mainly [[\u00c9minence grise|behind the scenes]] to implement the president's agenda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/192601-in-surprise-move-saraki-personally-submits-names-of-ministers-to-buhari.html|title=In surprise move, Saraki personally submits names of ministers to Buhari - Premium Times Nigeria|date=2015-11-03|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> In [[2019 Nigerian general election|2019]] with Buhari's re-election for a second term, he ordered his [[Cabinet of Nigeria|cabinet]] to channel all requests through Kyari's office.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2019/08/21/go-through-abba-kyari-to-see-me-buhari-directs-ministers/|title=Go through Abba Kyari to see me, Buhari directs ministers - P.M. News|website=www.pmnewsnigeria.com|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> Further enhancing his influence within government circles, and being labelled as the de facto head of government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://businessday.ng/lead-story/article/abba-kyari-prime-minister-in-a-presidential-system/|title=Abba Kyari: Prime minister in a presidential system|date=2019-08-25|website=Businessday NG|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, following a leaked memo, Kyari became embroiled in a public argument with the [[Nigerian Civil Service|Head of Civil Service]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelstv.com/2017/11/01/oyo-ita-kyari-heated-argument-villa/|title=Oyo-Ita, Kyari In Heated Argument At Presidential Villa|website=Channels Television|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> who was later removed from office and arrested.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/353112-breaking-buhari-sacks-head-of-service-oyo-ita.html|title=Buhari sacks Head of Service, Oyo-Ita - Premium Times Nigeria|date=2019-09-18|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenationonlineng.net/alleged-n570m-fraud-ex-head-of-service-oyo-ita-arrested/|title=Alleged N570m fraud: Ex-Head of Service Oyo-Ita arrested|last=Alli|first=Yusuf|date=2020-03-23|website=The Nation|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> In 2020, in another leaked memo, [[Babagana Monguno]] the [[National Security Advisor (Nigeria)|National Security Adviser]] accused Kyari of meddling in matters of national security.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/377757-updated-exclusive-buharis-team-in-disarray-as-nsa-monguno-declares-war-on-abba-kyari.html|title=UPDATED: EXCLUSIVE: Buhari\u2019s team in disarray as NSA Monguno declares war on Abba Kyari|last=Ogundipe|first=Samuel|date=2020-02-17|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nKyari died in the evening of 17 April 2020 in [[Lagos]], at the age of 67, after two weeks of testing positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://m.guardian.ng/breakingnews/buharis-chief-of-staff-abba-kyari-dies//|title=Buhari\u2019s Chief Of Staff Abba Kyari Dies|website=The Guardian Newspapers|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-18/nigerian-president-s-chief-of-staff-abba-kyari-dies-of-covid-19|title=Nigerian President\u2019s Chief of Staff Dies After Getting Virus|last=Soto|first=Alonso|date=18 April 2020|website=Bloomberg|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Honours and awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|[[Order of the Niger|Officer of the Order of the Niger]] (OON); [[File:Ribbon bar of the Order of the Niger.gif|frameless|59x59px]]\n|National honour in Nigeria\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kyari, Abba}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Nigerian Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Warwick]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the Niger]]\n[[Category:Nigerian lawyers]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{For|the Nigerian Army Brigadier who served as Governor of North-Central State|Abba Kyari (military general)}}\n{{short description|Nigerian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox Officeholder\n| name                = Abba Kyari\n| image               = Abba-Kyari2.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date|1952|09|23|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Borno State|Borno]], [[Northern Region, Nigeria|Northern Region]], [[British Nigeria]]<br>(now [[Borno State]], Nigeria)\n| death_date          = {{Death date and age|2020|4|17|1952|09|23|df=y}}\n| office1             = [[Chief of Staff to the President (Nigeria)| Chief of  Staff to the President]]\n| president1          = [[Muhammadu Buhari]]\n| term_start1         = 27 August 2015\n| term_end1           = 17 April 2020\n| predecessor1        = Jones Arogbofa\n| alma_mater          = [[Nigerian Law School]]<br>[[Harvard Business School]]<br>[[International Institute for Management Development]]\n| education           = [[University of Warwick]]<br>[[University of Cambridge]]\n| awards              = [[Order of the Niger]]\n| death_place         = [[Lagos]], Nigeria\n| honorific_suffix    = [[Order of the Niger|OON]]\n| spouse              = Hajiya Kulu Kyari\n| children            = 4\n}}\n\n'''Abba Kyari''' [[Order of the Niger|OON]] (23 September 1952 \u2013 17 April 2020)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/top-news/388646-exclusive-abba-kyaris-real-date-of-birth-uncovered.html |title=EXCLUSIVE: Abba Kyari's real date of birth uncovered |work=[[Premium Times]] |last=Ogundipe |first=Samuel |date=2020-04-18 |language=en-GB |access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> was a Nigerian Politician who served as Chief of Staff to [[President of Nigeria|President]] [[Muhammadu Buhari]].<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|last1=Bakare|first1=Tonye|title=Buhari appoints Lawal as SGF, Kyari as CoS|url=http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/2015/08/flash-buhari-appoints-lawal-as-sgf/|website=Guardian Nigeria|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Family and personal life==\n\n=== Early life and education ===\nKyari was born on 23 September 1952, to a [[Kanuri people|Kanuri]] family from [[Borno State|Borno]]. He was educated in St. Paul\u2019s College in [[Wusasa]], and later considered joining the [[Nigerian Army]] following advice from [[Mamman Daura]] and [[Ibrahim Tahir]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/opinion/columnists/ibrahim-tahir-a-personal-loss-2/|title=Ibrahim Tahir: A Personal Loss|last=Kyari|first=Abba|date=23 December 2009|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 1976, he met General [[Muhammadu Buhari]] who was then [[Governor of Borno State]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/features/for-the-record/to-my-friend-mallam-abba-kyari-buhari/|title=To my friend, Mallam Abba Kyari \u2013 Buhari|last=Buhari|first=Muhammadu|date=18 April 2020|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 1980, he graduated with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[sociology]] from the [[University of Warwick]], and also received a bachelor's degree in [[law]] from the [[University of Cambridge]].<ref name=\"Exxon-Mobil2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.exxonmobil.com.ng/Nigeria-English/PA/products_downstream_directors.aspx|title=Exxon Mobil Nigeria Board of Directors|website=Exxon Mobil|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref> In 1983, he was called to the [[Nigerian Bar Association|Nigerian Bar]] after attending the [[Nigerian Law School]].<ref name=\"TDLN\">{{cite web|last1=Aboyade |first1=Funke |title=From Dublin, Law School Set of \u201983 Plans Big |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/from-dublin-law-school-set-of-8217-83-plans-big/127530 |website=This Day Live Nigeria |accessdate=29 August 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016010128/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/from-dublin-law-school-set-of-8217-83-plans-big/127530 |archivedate=16 October 2012 }}</ref> \n\nIn 1984, he obtained a [[master's degree]] in law from the University of Cambridge.<ref name=\"Exxon-Mobil\">{{cite web|title=Exxon Mobil Nigeria Board of Directors|url=http://www.exxonmobil.com.ng/Nigeria-English/PA/products_downstream_directors.aspx|website=Exxon Mobil|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref> He later attended the [[International Institute for Management Development]] in [[Lausanne]], Switzerland and participated in the Program for Management Development at the [[Harvard Business School]], in 1992 and 1994, respectively.\n\n=== Family ===\nKyari was married to the sister-in-law of [[Ibrahim Tahir]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gamji.com/haruna/haruna303.htm|title=Tahir: The Death of a Radical Conservative|last=Haruna|first=Mohammed|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and had four children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/opinion/columnists/ibrahim-tahir-a-personal-loss-2/|title=Ibrahim Tahir: A Personal Loss|last=Kyari|first=Abba|date=23 December 2009|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Health ===\nOn 24 March 2020, it was made public that Kyari tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] on 23 March, following an official trip to Germany nine days before.<ref name=coronavirus>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/383571-coronavirus-abba-kyari-reportedly-tests-positive-kingibe-others-may-be-tested.html|title=UPDATED: Coronavirus: Abba Kyari reportedly tests positive; Kingibe, others may be tested|last=Owoseye|first=Ayodamola|date=2020-03-24|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> There were reports that he had been flown out of the country for treatment<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://desertherald.com/exclusive-buharis-chief-of-staff-abba-kyari-admitted-at-londons-hospital/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Buhari\u2019s Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari Admitted at London\u2019s Hospital|last=Herald|first=Desert|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>, and [[Reuters]] later reported he had \"a history of medical complications, including [[diabetes]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nigeria-idUSKBN21B1OT|title=Top Nigerian president aide, state governor test positive for coronavirus|date=2020-03-24|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-18|language=en}}</ref> On 29 March 2020, in an official statement, Kyari annouced he was being moved from isolation in [[Abuja]] to [[Lagos]] for \"preventive treatment\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/covid-19-why-i-moved-to-lagos-after-testing-positive-abba-kyari.html|title=Covid-19: Why I moved to Lagos after testing positive - Abba Kyari|date=2020-03-29|website=Daily Trust|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Professional career ==\nKyari worked for the law firm Fani-Kayode and Sowemimo for some time after his return to Nigeria.<ref name=\"Naij-FFK\">{{cite web|last1=Bolashodun|first1=Oluwatobi|title=Fani-Kayode Reacts To Abba Kyari's Appointment|url=https://www.naij.com/532624-read-fani-kayodes-reaction-abba-kyaris-appointment-buharis-cos.html|website=Naij|accessdate=29 August 2015}}</ref>  \n\nFrom 1988 to 1990, he was Editor with the New Africa Holdings Limited Kaduna.  \n\nIn 1990, he served as a Commissioner for Forestry and Animal Resources in [[Borno State]].  \n\nFrom 1990 to 1995, Kyari was the secretary to the board of African International Bank Limited, a subsidiary of [[Bank of Credit and Commerce International]]. \n\nKyari was an executive director in charge of management services at the [[United Bank for Africa]], and was later appointed the [[chief executive officer]]. In 2002, he was appointed a board director of [[Unilever Nigeria Plc|Unilever Nigeria]], and later served on the board of [[ExxonMobil|Exxon Mobil]] Nigeria.\n\n== Political career ==\nIn August 2015, Kyari was appointed [[Chief of Staff to the President (Nigeria)|Chief of Staff]] to [[President of Nigeria|President]] [[Muhammadu Buhari]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoguideafrica.com/2020/04/Abba-Kyari.html|title=Mallam Abba Kyari Biography, Age, Early Life, Family, Net Worth And More|last=Stanford|first=Igbo|website=Information Guide Africa|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/189095-breaking-buhari-appoints-sgf-chief-of-staff-others.html|title=Buhari appoints SGF, Chief of Staff, others - Premium Times Nigeria|date=2015-08-27|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n=== Power politics ===\nKyari was an influential figure within the Buhari administration.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punchng.com/men-of-power-nigerias-most-influential-power-brokers/|title=Men of power: Nigeria\u2019s most influential power brokers|last=Published|website=Punch Newspapers|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> During the administration's first term, he worked mainly [[\u00c9minence grise|behind the scenes]] to implement the president's agenda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/192601-in-surprise-move-saraki-personally-submits-names-of-ministers-to-buhari.html|title=In surprise move, Saraki personally submits names of ministers to Buhari - Premium Times Nigeria|date=2015-11-03|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> In [[2019 Nigerian general election|2019]] with Buhari's re-election for a second term, he ordered his [[Cabinet of Nigeria|cabinet]] to channel all requests through Kyari's office.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2019/08/21/go-through-abba-kyari-to-see-me-buhari-directs-ministers/|title=Go through Abba Kyari to see me, Buhari directs ministers - P.M. News|website=www.pmnewsnigeria.com|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> Further enhancing his influence within government circles, and being labelled as the de facto head of government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://businessday.ng/lead-story/article/abba-kyari-prime-minister-in-a-presidential-system/|title=Abba Kyari: Prime minister in a presidential system|date=2019-08-25|website=Businessday NG|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, following a leaked memo, Kyari became embroiled in a public argument with the [[Nigerian Civil Service|Head of Civil Service]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelstv.com/2017/11/01/oyo-ita-kyari-heated-argument-villa/|title=Oyo-Ita, Kyari In Heated Argument At Presidential Villa|website=Channels Television|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> who was later removed from office and arrested.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/353112-breaking-buhari-sacks-head-of-service-oyo-ita.html|title=Buhari sacks Head of Service, Oyo-Ita - Premium Times Nigeria|date=2019-09-18|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenationonlineng.net/alleged-n570m-fraud-ex-head-of-service-oyo-ita-arrested/|title=Alleged N570m fraud: Ex-Head of Service Oyo-Ita arrested|last=Alli|first=Yusuf|date=2020-03-23|website=The Nation|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> In 2020, in another leaked memo, [[Babagana Monguno]] the [[National Security Advisor (Nigeria)|National Security Adviser]] accused Kyari of meddling in matters of national security.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/377757-updated-exclusive-buharis-team-in-disarray-as-nsa-monguno-declares-war-on-abba-kyari.html|title=UPDATED: EXCLUSIVE: Buhari\u2019s team in disarray as NSA Monguno declares war on Abba Kyari|last=Ogundipe|first=Samuel|date=2020-02-17|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nKyari died in the evening of 17 April 2020 in [[Lagos]], at the age of 67, after testing positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://m.guardian.ng/breakingnews/buharis-chief-of-staff-abba-kyari-dies//|title=Buhari\u2019s Chief Of Staff Abba Kyari Dies|website=The Guardian Newspapers|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> His death is likely to create a [[power vacuum]] within the government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-18/nigerian-president-s-chief-of-staff-abba-kyari-dies-of-covid-19|title=Nigerian President\u2019s Chief of Staff Dies After Getting Virus|last=Soto|first=Alonso|date=18 April 2020|website=Bloomberg|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Honours and awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|[[Order of the Niger|Officer of the Order of the Niger]] (OON); [[File:Ribbon bar of the Order of the Niger.gif|frameless|59x59px]]\n|National honour in Nigeria\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kyari, Abba}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Nigerian Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Warwick]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the Niger]]\n[[Category:Nigerian lawyers]]\n", "name_user": "Menneth", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abba_Kyari_(politician)"}
